{"tid":1669863,"cid":5,"subCid":0,"title":"[核彈] 金融時報：維尼拍板三月換林奠","createTime":"2019-10-22T20:44:00.000Z","updateTime":"2019-10-23T05:06:07.000Z","uid":268038,"like":13,"dislike":152,"uniUserReply":117,"replies":[{"pid":"51c7b4ee52e4ed97262a81af0a5a4bf88a6a65db","tid":1669863,"uid":268038,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2019-10-22T20:44:00.000Z","msg":"<span style=\"font-size: xx-large;\"><strong><span style=\"color: blue;\">由唐唐或陳德霖補上</span></strong></span><img src=\"/assets/faces/pig/knife.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/pig/knife.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/pig/knife.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/pig/knife.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/pig/knife.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><br />\n<br />\nThe Chinese government is drawing up a plan to replace Carrie Lam, Hong Kong&rsquo;s leader, with an &ldquo;interim&rdquo; chief executive following violent protests against her administration, according to people briefed on the deliberations. <br />\n<br />\nThe people said that if Xi Jinping, China&rsquo;s president, decided to go ahead, Ms Lam&rsquo;s successor would be installed by March and cover the remainder of her term, which ends in 2022. They would not necessarily stay on for a full five-year term afterwards.<br />\n<br />\nWhen Tung Chee-hwa, Hong Kong&rsquo;s first Chinese chief executive, resigned in 2005, Donald Tsang, the territory&rsquo;s then most senior bureaucrat, served out the remainder of his term and was reappointed chief executive for a full five-year term in 2007. <br />\n<br />\n<br />\nLeading candidates to succeed Ms Lam include Norman Chan, former head of the Hong Kong Monetary Authority, and Henry Tang, son of a textile magnate who has also served as the territory&rsquo;s financial secretary and chief secretary for administration, the people added. <br />\n<br />\nMr Chan is one of the &ldquo;three Chans&rdquo; viewed as possible successors to Ms Lam. But the other two &mdash; Paul Chan, financial secretary, and Bernard Chan, convener of an &ldquo;executive council&rdquo; that advises Ms Lam &mdash; are viewed as being too close to her now discredited administration. <br />\n<br />\nThe Hong Kong Monetary Authority, which Norman Chan headed for a decade, is widely respected as an independent institution that has successfully managed the territory&rsquo;s US dollar currency peg for almost 40 years.<br />\n<br />\nMr Tang, meanwhile, only served under Ms Lam&rsquo;s predecessors. <br />\n<br />\n&ldquo;We have to look within at people who have served in government but also know how business operates here,&rdquo; said one prominent member of Hong Kong&rsquo;s pro-Beijing establishment. &ldquo;And of course they need to be trusted by Beijing.&rdquo; <br />\n<br />\n&ldquo;We needed a big bang but this government doesn&rsquo;t have any imagination,&rdquo; said a senior executive at one of Hong Kong&rsquo;s largest companies."},{"pid":"0342e044ce95543e4cdb6a11a3dbd27129fa14dd","tid":1669863,"uid":268038,"like":19,"dislike":1,"score":18,"quote":{"pid":"51c7b4ee52e4ed97262a81af0a5a4bf88a6a65db","tid":1669863,"uid":268038,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2019-10-22T20:44:00.000Z","msg":"<span style=\"font-size: xx-large;\"><strong><span style=\"color: blue;\">由唐唐或陳德霖補上</span></strong></span><img src=\"/assets/faces/pig/knife.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/pig/knife.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/pig/knife.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/pig/knife.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/pig/knife.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><br />\n<br />\nThe Chinese government is drawing up a plan to replace Carrie Lam, Hong Kong&rsquo;s leader, with an &ldquo;interim&rdquo; chief executive following violent protests against her administration, according to people briefed on the deliberations. <br />\n<br />\nThe people said that if Xi Jinping, China&rsquo;s president, decided to go ahead, Ms Lam&rsquo;s successor would be installed by March and cover the remainder of her term, which ends in 2022. They would not necessarily stay on for a full five-year term afterwards.<br />\n<br />\nWhen Tung Chee-hwa, Hong Kong&rsquo;s first Chinese chief executive, resigned in 2005, Donald Tsang, the territory&rsquo;s then most senior bureaucrat, served out the remainder of his term and was reappointed chief executive for a full five-year term in 2007. <br />\n<br />\n<br />\nLeading candidates to succeed Ms Lam include Norman Chan, former head of the Hong Kong Monetary Authority, and Henry Tang, son of a textile magnate who has also served as the territory&rsquo;s financial secretary and chief secretary for administration, the people added. <br />\n<br />\nMr Chan is one of the &ldquo;three Chans&rdquo; viewed as possible successors to Ms Lam. But the other two &mdash; Paul Chan, financial secretary, and Bernard Chan, convener of an &ldquo;executive council&rdquo; that advises Ms Lam &mdash; are viewed as being too close to her now discredited administration. <br />\n<br />\nThe Hong Kong Monetary Authority, which Norman Chan headed for a decade, is widely respected as an independent institution that has successfully managed the territory&rsquo;s US dollar currency peg for almost 40 years.<br />\n<br />\nMr Tang, meanwhile, only served under Ms Lam&rsquo;s predecessors. <br />\n<br />\n&ldquo;We have to look within at people who have served in government but also know how business operates here,&rdquo; said one prominent member of Hong Kong&rsquo;s pro-Beijing establishment. &ldquo;And of course they need to be trusted by Beijing.&rdquo; <br />\n<br />\n&ldquo;We needed a big bang but this government doesn&rsquo;t have any imagination,&rdquo; said a senior executive at one of Hong Kong&rsquo;s largest companies."},"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2019-10-22T20:44:57.000Z","msg":"<img src=\"https://na.cx/i/EzUW5CW.png\" data-t